    <div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='23317#1418398807'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-12-12T15:40:07+00:00">Dec 12, 2014 03:40 PM UTC</time> by <b>Vince Neal</b><a class="anchor" name="1418398807">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Thanks, all.  Setting to resolved.</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='23317#1418334195'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-12-11T21:43:15+00:00">Dec 11, 2014 09:43 PM UTC</time> by <b>Anand Padmanabhan</b><a class="anchor" name="1418334195">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Thanks for providing the necessary information. We will close out this ticket.</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='23317#1418152888'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-12-09T19:21:28+00:00">Dec 9, 2014 07:21 PM UTC</time> by <b>OSG-GOC</b><a class="anchor" name="1418152888">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>reply from&#58; berman@....

Answers to your question are inline below

eileen

________________________________
Incident State&#58; Work in Progress
Caller&#58; cd-srv-goc-ops
Assignment Group&#58; LBNE Support
Assigned To&#58;
Summary&#58;
Dear VO Managers,

The OSG security team is conducting a drill/audit of OSG VOs to check if VO users are actually signing Acceptable User Policy (AUP). As we mentioned in an email sometime ago OSG VOs are expected to ensure that they have an AUP and that their users are made aware of it periodically. Specifically, three conditions were outlined

1. If VO users have a certificate that is registered in its VOMS server, then the associated VOMS Admin interface or another equivalent system should have a valid VO AUP and the users are expected to read and accept the AUP atleast once a year, failing which the user much be suspended from the VO. The acceptance of AUP by the user needs to be recorded.
2. If the VO uses a pilot job framework (e.g. glideinWMS), and its users have ssh access to a glidein frontend (or equivalent) from where they submit jobs to OSG, then the login to the frontend system should display the usage conditions and provide a link to the VO AUP. Since it would be difficult to record acceptance during every login, a message displayed immediately after login should indicate that if users don&#39;t accept the AUP they should immediately exit and not submit jobs to OSG.
3. If VO uses a Science Gateway (or equivalent) system, then users of such gateway should be asked to accept the VO AUP during registration, and a link to the AUP should be made available during login. The acceptance of AUP by the user needs to be recorded during their registration, and text indicating that they accept AUP by logging in to the system should be displayed on the login page.

I selected two random users from your VOMS below.
/DC=com/DC=DigiCert-Grid/O=Open Science Grid/OU=People/CN=Ofer Rind 1423
/DC=com/DC=DigiCert-Grid/O=Open Science Grid/OU=People/CN=Brian Kirby 2737

Please send us the following information
(a) When they last signed the AUP. (Any information that would provide proof of the users having reviewed and signed the AUP is sufficient.)

Ofer Rind applied for VO membership on June 26, 2014, and went through the usual web sign-up form, and signed the AUP.
Brian Kirby did the same on August 29, 2014.

(b) A link to the AUP they signed.
<a href='https&#58;//voms.fnal.gov&#58;8443/voms/lbne/aup/load.action' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//voms.fnal.gov&#58;8443/voms/lbne/aup/load.action</a>

(c) A list of users, if any, who have not signed the AUP and are still enabled in VOMS (i.e. not suspended), and what action (if any) has been taken against them.

<div id='show_1958158503' class=''><button class="btn">Show More</button></div><div class='detail hidden' id='detail_1958158503'>we require all users to sign the AUP.  as mentioned in a previous email, there was an issue last January which has bee resolved.  This January all the users who were renewed last year will have the signing expire and will have to resign the AUP themselves.

(d) Do LBNE users have their own certificates which they are required to use to submit jobs (even when using glidein) on the OSG. If not, how are these users without certificates informed of and consent to AUP.

as Tom mentioned -

Our new-user web signup form requires a KCA certificate.  New users are pointed to this signin page

<a href='https&#58;//voms.fnal.gov&#58;8443/voms/lbne/home/login.action' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//voms.fnal.gov&#58;8443/voms/lbne/home/login.action</a>

if their certs are unkown to VOMS for the LBNE VO, then they get a signup form and are requested to sign this AUP&#58;

<a href='https&#58;//voms.fnal.gov&#58;8443/voms/lbne/aup/load.action' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//voms.fnal.gov&#58;8443/voms/lbne/aup/load.action</a>

Does this answer your questions?

eileen and Tom

Best
Anand
On behalf of OSG Security

