<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; <a href='https&#58;//voms.fnal.gov&#58;8443/voms/lbne/aup/load.action' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//voms.fnal.gov&#58;8443/voms/lbne/aup/load.action</a></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Brett applied for VO membership recently with an OSG cert on July 1, 2014, and as far as I can</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; tell, went through the sign-in</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; form linked above and should have seen and clicked &#34;yes&#34; on the AUP linked immediately above.  </font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; The VOMS admin interface</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; says the AUP was signed 160 days ago and it will expire in 204 days.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;  He has an older membership using his KCA identity.  The AUP on this expired January 30, 2014,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; and his</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; membership was suspended.  On January 30, 2014, more than</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; half of the users in the LBNE VO had their AUP expire and were suspended.  This is largely due</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; to the old version of VOMS</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; giving users only 24 hours (regardless of holidays or weekends) between being notified and being</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; suspended.  Eileen</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; and I complained about this since many of our collaborators have difficulty obtaining KCA</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; certificates on their non-Fermilab</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; computers and the 24-hour window was not enough time for busy users to divert their attention to</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; figuring out how to</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; install KCA certs.   I re-instated the suspended accounts back in January to keep people</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; working.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; VOMS was upgraded in May 2014 or thereabouts to a system that gives two weeks advance notice and</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; no ability for admins</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; to update users&#39; AUP signing.    So some users may not have signed an AUP since their initial</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; signin and may have forgotten,</font>
